<tr><th colspan="2">TIE BREAKING WITHIN A POOL</th></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2">Ties in pool standings will be broken by employing a tiebreaker. If more than two teams are involved in the tie, the first team to move ahead of the remaining teams will be awarded the highest place, and the tiebreakers continued until all ties are broken.</td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top">A.</td><td>Head-to-head result between the teams (if they played each other).</td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top">B.</td><td>Best goal differential (maximum of plus or minus four per Cup game; example, if a team wins its three games by 5-0, 6-1 and 7-2, its goal differential is +12, reflecting the max. of four per game).</td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top">C</td><td>Most goals scored (maximum credit of four per Cup game, so no more than 12 in all).</td></tr>
